01:29:57.097 --> 01:29:58.680
with is like, we
want to animate this,

01:29:58.680 --> 01:30:00.950
because I don't want to
explain it on a camera.

01:30:00.950 --> 01:30:03.200
GEORGE ZAIDAN: Or I can't
say this long of a paragraph

01:30:03.200 --> 01:30:04.030
without stumbling.

01:30:04.030 --> 01:30:05.780
AUDIENCE: Or we'll
take their script away,

01:30:05.780 --> 01:30:08.040
and they'll be like
I need to have it.

01:30:08.040 --> 01:30:09.650
I can't do it.

01:30:09.650 --> 01:30:11.930
That is so not true.

01:30:11.930 --> 01:30:15.220
You can't actually prove
that you can't do it.

01:30:15.220 --> 01:30:18.530
And we want your
faces to be on camera,

01:30:18.530 --> 01:30:22.660
and we can talk about
this more, but I

01:30:22.660 --> 01:30:25.817
think that if you do
too much of the pictures

01:30:25.817 --> 01:30:27.400
and the voiceovers
and the animations,

01:30:27.400 --> 01:30:31.320
then we go back to
that Siri litmus test.

01:30:31.320 --> 01:30:35.630
Or if we swap you out for
anyone else to do this video,

01:30:35.630 --> 01:30:37.420
it's not going to
make a big difference.

01:30:37.420 --> 01:30:39.086
And I don't know if
you're OK with that,

01:30:39.086 --> 01:30:41.570
but I certainly feel like
you have compelling enough

01:30:41.570 --> 01:30:42.380
of a perspective.

01:30:42.380 --> 01:30:46.330
Didn't you say you used to work
for an orthodontics company?

01:30:46.330 --> 01:30:49.890
Yeah, that is a really
unique perspective,

01:30:49.890 --> 01:30:53.897
both from the industry--
and my mom's a dentist.

01:30:53.897 --> 01:30:56.230
So I used to work at her
office, and I had braces twice.

01:30:56.230 --> 01:31:00.717
And I know for sure that there's
so much fascinating information

01:31:00.717 --> 01:31:03.300
about that that you would know
from that perspective that most

01:31:03.300 --> 01:31:03.860
people don't.

01:31:06.488 --> 01:31:09.920
You can make a video that
a lot of people can't.

01:31:09.920 --> 01:31:13.800
And I would hesitate
to let you go

01:31:13.800 --> 01:31:19.000
on thinking that your
video should be that way.

01:31:19.000 --> 01:31:20.500
GEORGE ZAIDAN: And
that's not to say

01:31:20.500 --> 01:31:25.800
that like it's just going to
be you on camera or any of you.

01:31:25.800 --> 01:31:27.800
That's not to say
the entire video

01:31:27.800 --> 01:31:31.380
is going to be from here
to here, 100% of the time,

01:31:31.380 --> 01:31:33.730
talking.

01:31:33.730 --> 01:31:37.107
We know that that doesn't
make for compelling video.

01:31:37.107 --> 01:31:39.440
You want to have the person
doing something, interacting

01:31:39.440 --> 01:31:42.540
with their environment, being in
an interesting place, whatever.

01:31:42.540 --> 01:31:49.030
There are lots of ways to
compliment the fact that--

01:31:49.030 --> 01:31:50.390
let me back up a second.

01:31:50.390 --> 01:31:53.180
The human-to-human--
ideally, you

01:31:53.180 --> 01:31:54.710
want to transmit information.

01:31:54.710 --> 01:31:56.810
One person sits down
and talks to another,

01:31:56.810 --> 01:32:00.892
that's like the idealized
way to engage someone, convey

01:32:00.892 --> 01:32:02.850
information, talk about
an interesting subject,

01:32:02.850 --> 01:32:05.840
whatever it is.

01:32:05.840 --> 01:32:07.340
Obviously, video
gives you the power

01:32:07.340 --> 01:32:10.710
to do that to a wide audience
at once, and it's remote,

01:32:10.710 --> 01:32:12.310
but there is
something about seeing

01:32:12.310 --> 01:32:16.850
someone's face, and
expressions, and intonations,

01:32:16.850 --> 01:32:20.890
and something that really
draws you into the material.

01:32:20.890 --> 01:32:23.640
But that having
been said, you don't

01:32:23.640 --> 01:32:25.500
want to just stay
on that person's

01:32:25.500 --> 01:32:29.230
face for the whole video
and not show anything else.

01:32:29.230 --> 01:32:32.790
But that's our job, as
producers and directors,

01:32:32.790 --> 01:32:36.230
is to figure out where it makes
sense to just do a simple head

01:32:36.230 --> 01:32:38.740
shot of someone talking
versus where it makes sense

01:32:38.740 --> 01:32:40.161
to cut away for an animation.

01:32:40.161 --> 01:32:41.910
If you're talking about
like teeth moving,

01:32:41.910 --> 01:32:44.810
that might be a
perfect place to do it.

01:32:44.810 --> 01:32:47.030
Versus where to do
a demo or whatever

01:32:47.030 --> 01:32:50.160
it is to keep visual variety and
interest throughout the video.

01:32:50.160 --> 01:32:53.220
But yes?

01:32:53.220 --> 01:32:55.230
AUDIENCE: That was a
tangent-- an important one.

01:32:55.230 --> 01:32:57.438
AUDIENCE: No, I think it's
actually really important.

01:32:57.438 --> 01:33:00.320
AUDIENCE: Well, it's also
a segue into [INAUDIBLE].

01:33:00.320 --> 01:33:02.466
AUDIENCE: Yeah.

01:33:02.466 --> 01:33:05.764
I have all these graduate
fellows who work for me.

01:33:05.764 --> 01:33:09.093
We do workshops all over campus
and our biggest credibility,

01:33:09.093 --> 01:33:11.830
and why we can give our
workshops,and why people care,

01:33:11.830 --> 01:33:14.640
and listen to them is because
we give workshops on how

01:33:14.640 --> 01:33:17.850
to succeed with the National
Science Foundation awards from

01:33:17.850 --> 01:33:20.620
people who have
actually earned them.

01:33:20.620 --> 01:33:21.400
We're authentic.

01:33:21.400 --> 01:33:22.180
I did this.

01:33:22.180 --> 01:33:24.300
I'm going to tell you what
I did to be successful.

01:33:24.300 --> 01:33:26.027
That's what you have
that's so powerful.

01:33:26.027 --> 01:33:26.610
I'm a student.

01:33:26.610 --> 01:33:29.310
I'm studying this with this
really great institute,

01:33:29.310 --> 01:33:32.480
and I'm going to share with you
how I think about something.

01:33:32.480 --> 01:33:36.010
That's like the most authentic
you can be, is being you.

01:33:38.920 --> 01:33:43.030
It would be a shame to go to
someone who's inauthentic,

01:33:43.030 --> 01:33:46.195
like someone we don't know
like a movie star, when

01:33:46.195 --> 01:33:50.683
you have this incredible
credibility by just being you.

01:33:50.683 --> 01:33:52.251
That's so powerful.

01:33:55.080 --> 01:33:57.380
GEORGE ZAIDAN: OK.

01:33:57.380 --> 01:33:59.190
AUDIENCE: Sorry, you
guys are so cool.

01:33:59.190 --> 01:34:01.230
GEORGE ZAIDAN: No,
you're absolutely right.

01:34:01.230 --> 01:34:02.150
That is correct.

01:34:05.125 --> 01:34:07.000
AUDIENCE: But now it's
about how to structure

01:34:07.000 --> 01:34:10.570
